tspan.tspan: 1. Research roadmap of Biophysics Research Division FMIPA ITB is directed to study
advanced physical mechanisms in biosystems (molecules, cells, organs) using
quantitative methods and measurements.
2. It includes characterization, modeling, method development and their
application. The study is focused on the fields of molecular biophysics, membrane
biophysics and radiation biophysics and medical physics. In molecular biophysics,
research is carried out to study structure-function relationships, the basic
principles of biochemical reaction happened in many biosystems. Current
research in this field is focused on bioluminescence and biosensor.
3. In membrane biophysics, research is carried out to study transport
phenomenon, the basics principle of regulation system and physical
measurements in bio-systems. Current research in this field is focused on the
effect of pollutants to ion transport through cell membranes and the application of
cellular automata methods for fluid dynamics through membranes.
4. In radiation biophysics and medical physics, research is carried out to study the
interaction of radiation with biological materials and the application of physics to
the function of the human body and in the practice of medicine.
5. Current research in this field is focused on the development of medical imaging
methods such as MRI, CT and USG, the development of medical treatment planning
methods, nuclear medicine and networking in hospital.
